Section 7.2: Servicer Continuation Triggers

In this Agreement, the term "Servicer" shall refer to the party responsible for administering the Loan, and this clause outlines the circumstances under which such responsibility may persist or be transferred. Initially, it is agreed that the Servicer's role shall continue unless any of the following events occur:

1. The Servicer fails to comply with its obligations under this Agreement, as set forth in Section 5.2, for a continuous period of thirty (30) days or more;
2. The Servicer becomes unable or unwilling to perform its duties under this Agreement due to bankruptcy, insolvency, or reorganization, either judicially or otherwise;
3. The Servicer ceases to be a qualified entity to serve as the Loan's administrator, as determined by regulatory bodies with relevant jurisdiction;
4. There is a change in control of the Servicer that materially affects its ability or willingness to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement;
5. Upon mutual agreement between the Borrower and the Servicer, the Servicer may elect to transfer its duties to another qualified entity, subject to approval by the Lender.

In all cases where the Servicer's role is terminated or transferred, the Servicer shall remain liable for any outstanding obligations under this Agreement, including but not limited to, any losses, damages, or liabilities incurred as a result of its actions prior to the termination or transfer.

