Section 9.10 Cap Collateral Account Obligations. In the event that the Cap Counterparty is not required to post collateral under the terms of the Cap Agreement, but elects to do so voluntarily, upon written direction and notification of such election, the Servicer shall establish a segregated account (the “Cap Collateral Account”) at a Qualified Institution that:

1. Is not affiliated with the Cap Counterparty;
2. Has total assets exceeding $10,000,000,000; and
3. The account title reflects the Cap Counterparty as depositor and entitlement holder.

If the selected custodian no longer satisfies these requirements, the Issuer, the Servicer, and the Cap Counterparty shall have a reasonable period of time, not to exceed sixty (60) calendar days, to transfer the Cap Collateral Account and any collateral posted therein to another financial institution meeting the specified criteria. The Cap Collateral Account will be governed by a tri-party account control agreement (the “Control Agreement”) between the Cap Counterparty, the Issuer, and the selected custodian (the "Cap Custodian").

The Control Agreement shall provide that:

1. The Cap Counterparty may originate entitlement orders and instructions regarding the Cap Collateral Account as long as the Issuer has not delivered a notice to the Cap Counterparty and the Cap Custodian stating that the Issuer will exercise exclusive control over the account;
2. Following delivery of such notice, the Cap Custodian shall comply with any instructions or entitlement orders issued by the Issuer without further consent from the Cap Counterparty;
3. The Control Agreement may only be terminated:
   a) Upon five (5) Business Days' notice from the Cap Counterparty to the Cap Custodian and the Issuer, designating an "Early Termination Date" for all Transactions (as defined in the Cap Agreement), if the Issuer is deemed a "Defaulting Party" (as defined in the Cap Agreement) or the sole "Affected Party" (as defined in the Cap Agreement) with respect to a "Termination Event" (as defined in the Cap Agreement), unless such termination is contested by the Issuer within said five (5) Business Days;
   b) Under any other circumstances agreed upon by the parties.

The Issuer acknowledges that it shall not exercise exclusive control over, or originate entitlement orders or instructions for the disposition of funds with respect to, the Cap Collateral Account unless the conditions for the exercise of its rights and remedies under the Cap Agreement are met and such action is taken for the purpose of exercising such rights and remedies. Withdrawals from, or applications of funds on deposit in, or otherwise to the credit of, the Cap Collateral Account shall only be permitted:

1. For the satisfaction of obligations of the Cap Counterparty to the Issuer under the Cap Agreement;
2. To return collateral to the Cap Counterparty when and as required by the Cap Agreement or applicable law; and
3. As approved in writing by all parties to the Control Agreement.

Investment earnings on the Cap Collateral Account, if any, will be distributed to the Cap Counterparty.
